'''Charles Henry Ritche''' ({{Circa|1886/87}}<U+2013>1958) was an [[Anglican ministry|Anglican clergyman]] who served in both the [[Church of England]] and the [[Scottish Episcopal Church]].

== Life ==
He was educated at [[St John's College, Cambridge]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|B.A.]] 1910; [[Master of Arts|M.A.]] 1914) and [[Leeds Clergy School]] (1910).{{sfn|Bertie|2000|loc=''Scottish Episcopal Clergy'', p. 417}} He was [[Holy orders|ordained]] in the [[Anglican ministry]] as a [[deacon]] in 1911 and a [[priest]] in 1912.{{sfn|Bertie|2000|loc=''Scottish Episcopal Clergy'', p. 417}} His first [[Pastoral care|pastoral]] appointment was a [[curate]] at St. Michael's Church, [[Chester Square]], [[County of London|London]], 1911<U+2013>14.{{sfn|Bertie|2000|loc=''Scottish Episcopal Clergy'', p. 417}} In 1915, he married Marjorie Alice Stewart. During the [[World War I|First World War]], he served as a temporary [[chaplain]] in the [[Royal Navy]], 1914<U+2013>19.{{sfn|Bertie|2000|loc=''Scottish Episcopal Clergy'', p. 417}} After the war, he was briefly a [[curate]] at [[Dunedin]], [[New Zealand]], 1921<U+2013>22, before returning to England where was a curate at [[St Martin-in-the-Fields]], [[County of London|London]], 1922<U+2013>27.{{sfn|Bertie|2000|loc=''Scottish Episcopal Clergy'', p. 417}} He was then [[Rector (ecclesiastical)|Rector]] of [[Church of St John the Evangelist, Edinburgh|St John's, Edinburgh]], 1927<U+2013>39,{{sfn|Bertie|2000|loc=''Scottish Episcopal Clergy'', p. 417}} and a [[Canon (priest)|canon]] of [[St Mary's Cathedral, Edinburgh (Episcopal)|St Mary's Cathedral, Edinburgh]], 1937<U+2013>39.{{sfn|Bertie|2000|loc=''Scottish Episcopal Clergy'', pp. 417 and 571}} His final appointment was 
[[Archdeacon of Northumberland]], 1939<U+2013>54.{{sfn|Bertie|2000|loc=''Scottish Episcopal Clergy'', p. 417}}<ref>{{Who's Who |surname=Ritchie |othernames=Rev. Canon Charles Henry |id=U242320 |type=was |volume=1920<U+2013>2014 |edition=April 2014 online |accessed=30 May 2014}}</ref> He died in [[Polzeath]], [[Cornwall]] on 8 September 1958, aged 71.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://probatesearch.service.gov.uk/Calendar/GetImgSrc?filePath=%2F1958%2FR%2F007178_rispin_1958.Png |title=Calendar of Wills and Administrations |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |year=1958 |page= 237 |website=Find a will |access-date=11 March 2015}}</ref>

